defaultAFS0061defaultWritten evidence submitted bydefault COMPASS-Suffolk defaultCOMPASS was a parent-led campaign group local to the Great Cornard Upper School
default (GCUS) pyramid in South Suffolk. The group formed in the autumn of 2010 to ensure that there was open debate on a proposed Free School in Stoke by Nayland (a village in the catchment area for GCUS) and to inform local parents and community members about t
defaulthe implications of a new Free School in the area. 
